# Uploads Directory

This directory stores all uploaded files (receipts, scans, documents, etc.) attached to various cost records.

## Security
- Files are stored with unique filenames to prevent conflicts
- Original filenames are preserved in the database
- Access controlled through API authentication
- MIME type validation prevents malicious file uploads

## Structure
Files are stored flat in this directory with naming convention:
```
{slugified-original-name}-{unique-id}.{extension}
```

Example:
```
fuel-receipt-abc123def456.jpg
mot-certificate-xyz789ghi012.pdf
service-invoice-mno345pqr678.pdf
```

## Backup
Ensure this directory is included in your backup strategy as it contains important documents.

## Permissions
The directory should have write permissions for the web server user:
```bash
chmod 755 uploads/
```

## Gitignore
This directory is gitignored to prevent committing uploaded files to version control.
